CODE OF CONDUCT
Copyright (c) 2025 宋子桓（Song Zihuan）

By submitting a Pull Request (PR) or any form of contribution to this project,
you agree to abide by the terms of this Code of Conduct.

We are committed to providing a friendly, safe, and welcoming environment for all,
regardless of background, identity, or experience level.

---

1. Expected Behavior
--------------------
- Be respectful, constructive, and professional in all communications.
- Use inclusive language and avoid sarcasm, personal attacks, or demeaning remarks.
- Respect differing viewpoints and experiences.
- Gracefully accept constructive criticism.
- Focus on what is best for the community and the project.
- Show empathy and kindness toward other contributors.

---

2. Unacceptable Behavior
------------------------
Examples include, but are not limited to:
- Harassment, intimidation, or discrimination based on gender, gender identity, 
  sexual orientation, disability, physical appearance, body size, race, religion, 
  nationality, or technical choices.
- Deliberate misgendering, deadnaming, or use of unwelcome sexual attention.
- Publishing others’ private information (e.g., physical or email address) without 
  explicit permission.
- Threats of violence, incitement of harm, or encouraging self-harm.
- Disruptive behavior, trolling, or sustained negativity that detracts from productive 
  collaboration.
- Attempts to circumvent moderation decisions or project governance.

---

3. Reporting Violations
-----------------------
If you witness or experience behavior that violates this Code of Conduct, please report it:

  Email: report@song-zh.com

Reports may be submitted anonymously. All reports will be reviewed promptly and handled 
confidentially by the project maintainers.

In your report, please include:
  - Your contact info (optional, if you want follow-up)
  - Names/links of involved parties (if known)
  - Description of the incident
  - Screenshots, logs, or links (if available)

---

4. Enforcement Guidelines
-------------------------
Project maintainers will:
  - Review all reports with seriousness and fairness.
  - Protect reporter confidentiality to the extent possible.
  - Take appropriate action, which may include:
      • Warning the offender
      • Editing or deleting inappropriate content
      • Temporarily or permanently banning from project spaces
      • Rejection or revert of contributions

Decisions are final and not subject to public debate.

---

5. Scope
--------
This Code of Conduct applies to all project spaces, including:
  - GitHub/GitLab issues, PRs, discussions, wikis
  - Project mailing lists, forums, chat rooms (Discord, Slack, Gitter, etc.)
  - In-person or virtual events associated with the project

---

6. Responsibility & Acknowledgement
-----------------------------------
By submitting a Pull Request (PR), Issue, Comment, or any contribution to this repository,
you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to be bound by this Code of Conduct.

Violations may result in rejection of contributions or removal from project spaces,
without liability to the project, its maintainers, or hosting platforms.

This document does not create a contractual relationship, but serves as a condition 
of participation in the project’s collaborative spaces.

---

Thank you for helping to build a respectful and productive open source community.